description: Unknown. Originally attested in Southern US dialects. Suggested origins include:

verbs.description: mosey (third-person singular simple present moseys, present participle moseying, simple past and past participle moseyed)

entries.meaning: (chiefly US, dialectal) To set off, get going; to start a journey.
(chiefly US, dialectal) To go off quickly: to hurry up.
(chiefly US, dialectal) To amble; to walk or proceed in a leisurely manner.
